  "text": "The gRPC health check protocol compliance implementation is distributed across Envoy and gRPC repositories. The primary implementation in Envoy is located in source/extensions/health_checkers/grpc/ with GrpcHealthCheckerImpl (health_checker_impl.h/cc) implementing the health check client using the grpc.health.v1.Health service defined in the gRPC repository at src/proto/grpc/health/v1/health.proto. The protocol defines HealthCheckRequest and HealthCheckResponse messages, where HealthCheckResponse contains a ServingStatus enum with values UNKNOWN, SERVING, NOT_SERVING, and SERVICE_UNKNOWN. Envoy's GrpcActiveHealthCheckSession class handles the request/response cycle: onInterval() initiates a health check by creating a HealthCheckRequest with optional service_name; decodeHeaders/decodeData/decodeTrailers methods parse the gRPC response; isHealthCheckSucceeded() evaluates success based on gRPC status being OK and response status being SERVING; onRpcComplete() reports the result; and logHealthCheckStatus() logs the health status. Status mapping between HTTP and gRPC is handled by Envoy's Grpc::Utility::httpToGrpcStatus() in source/common/grpc/status.cc, following the gRPC specification for HTTP-to-gRPC status code mapping. The gRPC server-side implementation in src/cpp/server/health/default_health_check_service.cc provides the Health service with Check and Watch RPC handlers, using DecodeRequest() to parse incoming HealthCheckRequest and EncodeResponse() to serialize HealthCheckResponse with the appropriate ServingStatus. The health discovery service (source/common/upstream/health_discovery_service.h/cc) integrates health check reporting through HDS protocol."
}

